==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffragist
<hw>Suf"fra*gist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who possesses or exercises the political right of suffrage; a
voter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who has certain opinions or desires about the
political right of suffrage; <as>as, a woman
<ex>suffragist</ex></as>.</def><-- if female, usu. suffragette. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is curious that . . . Louisa Castelefort should be obliged
after her marriage immediately to open her doors and turn ultra liberal,
or an universal <qex>suffragist</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Miss
Edgeworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffrago</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
